            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1681305383283-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1681305383283-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once browned, add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and <strong>dried thyme</strong> to the pan with the <strong>tomato paste</strong> and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong> and cook for 1-2 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>red wine paste</strong> and <strong>vegetable stock mix </strong>with the <strong>chopped tomatoes </strong>and 150ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[250ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Cook for 5-7 min further or until the sauce has thickened and the carrot is completely softened</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1681305388601-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1681305388601-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
